    <fr:title text="git bisect">
      <html:code>git bisect</html:code>
    </fr:title>
    <fr:meta name="author">false</fr:meta>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Useful tool for finding a breaking commit. Writeup taken from <fr:link href="https://github.com/stas00/the-art-of-debugging/tree/master/methodology" type="external">here</fr:link>.</html:p><html:p>Use two terminals. One is used for the bisection process and the other is used to run the program to tell whether the current commit is good or bad.</html:p><html:ol><html:li>Start with <html:code>git bisect start</html:code> to initialize the bisection process.</html:li>
  <html:li>Find a good commit and mark it with <html:code>git bisect good &lt;commit&gt;</html:code>.</html:li>
  <html:li>Run <html:code>git bisect bad &lt;commit&gt;</html:code> to mark the bad commit.</html:li>
  <html:li>Repeat until you find the breaking commit.</html:li>
  <html:li>Use <html:code>git bisect reset</html:code> to restore to the state you started from.</html:li></html:ol>
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/kellenkanarios/" title="Kellen Kanarios" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/kellenkanarios/" display-uri="kellenkanarios" type="local">Kellen Kanarios</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2026</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Remark</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
Can use <html:code>git bisect skip</html:code> to skip a specific commit, or <html:code>git bisect visualize --oneline</html:code> to see current progress.
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
</fr:mainmatter>
